TEXT(beginproblem());

##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#

Context("Numeric");
#given
$g = 9.81;
$h = random(300, 500, 100);
$W = random(10000, 15000, 1000);


#computation
$m = $W/($g*$h);


$imagescale = 0.4;
$width = $imagescale*1268;
$height = $imagescale*2118;
#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.05,
tolType=>'relative');

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

To increase the rate of climb, a ballast is dropped from the hot-air balloon.

If the ballast falls [`[$h]`] [`m`] from the balloon before hitting the ground and gravity does [`[$W]`] [`J`] of work on it, what is the mass of the ballast?

(Assume [`g = 9.81`] [`m/s^2`], neglect air resistance)


[@ image( "21-P-WE-GD-003.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*


[`m_{ballast} =`]  [_____]{"$m"} [`kg`]

END_PGML

